sequenceDiagram
    title Scenario 2: Connect with Planning Department with Identity Verification
    
    actor User as Użytkownik
    participant System as Centrala<br/>Telefoniczna
    
    Note over User,System: Language Selection
    User->>+System: Calls the exchange
    System->>User: Witamy w centrali Uniwersytetu.<br/>Welcome to University exchange.<br/>Dla języka polskiego naciśnij 1.<br/>For English press 2.
    User->>System: Presses 2 (English)
    System->>User: You selected English.
    
    Note over User,System: Main Menu
    System->>User: Main menu:<br/>1 - Directory<br/>2 - Planning Department<br/>3 - Registrar<br/>4 - Operator<br/>0 - Repeat menu
    User->>System: Presses 2 (Planning Department)
    
    Note over User,System: <<extend>> Identity Verification
    System->>User: Planning Department requires verification.<br/>Please enter your PESEL number<br/>followed by hash.
    User->>System: Enters PESEL (11 digits) + #
    System->>System: Validates PESEL format
    
    alt PESEL format valid
        System->>User: Please enter your date of birth<br/>in format DDMMYYYY followed by hash.
        User->>System: Enters date (e.g., 15031995) + #
        System->>System: Verifies PESEL + date of birth
        
        alt Verification successful
            System->>User: Verification successful.
            
            Note over User,System: Connection
            System->>User: Connecting to Planning Department.<br/>Please hold...
            System->>System: Routes call to Planning Department
            System->>-User: Thank you for calling.
        else Verification failed
            System->>User: Verification failed.<br/>Returning to main menu.
            System->>User: Main menu:<br/>1 - Directory<br/>2 - Planning Department...
        end
    else PESEL format invalid
        System->>User: Invalid PESEL format.<br/>Please try again.
        User->>System: Enters PESEL + #
    end
    
    Note right of System: Extension point: Identity verification<br/>Required for sensitive department access<br/><br/>Conversational principles:<br/>- Cooperation: Step-by-step guidance<br/>- Context: Language maintained<br/>- Brevity: Clear instructions<br/>- Error handling with retry option
